Problem: On small screens, the footer's language dropdown extended beyond the viewport. The top entries became unreachable and the user couldn't scroll inside the menu.Actual development process: Reproduced the issue by resizing the window and inspecting the menu's computed styles. Confirmed the list had no height constraint and inherited positioning that didn't keep it within the viewport. Implemented a scoped CSS class on the dropdown <ul> with max-height: 60vh, overflow-y: auto, and overscroll-behavior: contain; also constrained width to avoid horizontal overflow. Verified that all languages remain accessible via internal scrolling on narrow windows.Maintainer interaction: Submitted PR with before/after screenshots and a CSS diff. Maintainer acknowledged the UI regression and approved after confirming no regressions on desktop breakpoints.Outcome: Merged - deployed to production.Height Spinner Allowed Negative Values [Ziqi Lin]

